  "id": "019d32f3-6dee-7921-8fa9-5a762791962e",
  "content": "# PostgresStore tsvector (Phase 2b) -- Design Decisions (Updated 2026-03-28)\n\n## What: Implement FullTextSearchable for PostgresStore using native PostgreSQL tsvector.\n\n## Key Decisions:\n1. GENERATED ALWAYS AS (to_tsvector('english', content)) STORED is the correct approach. Despite to_tsvector being STABLE volatility, PostgreSQL 12+ accepts it in generated columns. Verified empirically on PG 17. Zero application-side tsvector maintenance needed.\n2. search_text() uses ts_rank_cd (cover density ranking) via lateral join pattern to evaluate plainto_tsquery once per query. Scores are raw positive values; BM25Searcher normalizes.\n3. Tier filtering matches vector search: only hot + warm entries are searched. Cold and forgotten entries are excluded for consistency with the composable pipeline.\n4. Explicit column list in SELECT (no SELECT *) to avoid fetching the tsv column unnecessarily.\n5. Empty/whitespace queries short-circuit without hitting PostgreSQL.\n\n## Alternatives rejected:\n- pg_bm25 extension: adds external dependency, not in standard pgvector image\n- Trigger-based tsvector: more complex, no advantage over GENERATED for this use case\n- SELECT *: wastes bandwidth transferring tsv column data that is never used",
  "source_version": "mcp",
